    <p>Last updated: June 25, 2025</p>

    <p><strong>HerCalendar</strong> is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what personal data we collect, how we use it, and your rights as a user of our application.</p>

    <h5>1. Information We Collect</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Your email address and username when you register</li>
        <li>Cycle tracking data such as period start dates and cycle length</li>
        <li>Login and account activity (for security purposes)</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>2. How We Use Your Data</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide personalized cycle tracking predictions</li>
        <li>To allow you to manage your cycle history</li>
        <li>To ensure account security and provide support</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>3. Data Storage and Security</h5>
    <p>Your data is stored in a secure Azure SQL database and protected using industry-standard security practices. Access is restricted to authenticated users only. Admin access is role-based and monitored.</p>

    <h5>4. Sharing of Data</h5>
    <p>We do <strong>not</strong> share your personal data with third parties. Your data stays private unless required by law or with your explicit consent.</p>

    <h5>5. Your Rights</h5>
    <p>You may:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Request a copy of your data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your account and data</li>
        <li>Update or correct your personal information at any time</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>6. Contact</h5>
    <p>If you have questions or requests regarding your privacy, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:brandonrock8404@gmail.com">brandonrock8404@gmail.com</a></p>

    <p>By using HerCalendar, you agree to this Privacy Policy.</p>
</main>

